dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.systemtemplate.fibex.fibex4can.cantopology

Interface ICanControllerConfigurationRequirements

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAbstractCanCommunicationControllerAttributes, IEntity

    public interface ICanControllerConfigurationRequirements
extends IEntity, IAbstractCanCommunicationControllerAttributes
    ICanControllerConfigurationRequirements: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    This element allows the specification of ranges for the CAN Bit Timing configuration parameters. These ranges are taken as requirements and have to be respected by the ECU developer.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

      • getMaxSyncJumpWidth

        double getMaxSyncJumpWidth()
        Query the value of the attribute MaxSyncJumpWidth.

        The max. Synchronization Jump Width value as a percentage of the total bit time. The (Re-)Synchronization Jump Width (SJW) defines how far a resynchronization may move the Sample Point inside the limits defined by the Phase Buffer Segments to compensate for edge phase errors.

        Returns:
        The value or null
